ppunctuations.ppunctuation:
Executed: not quite regularly;
Usage: not always logical.
Dividers:
I. Colon;
colon with short lines above and below (e.g. fols.: 1r, ls. 4, 5, 9, 10, 13; 4r, l.3; 25v, ls. 3, 7, 11, 12).
II. Four dot asterisk (e.g. fols.: 35v, l.2; 41v, ls.3, 7; fol. 43v, ls. 1, 5, 8, 10);
nine dot asterisk (used throughout the text);
more four dot asterisks (esp. fol. 44r, l.11).

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra; 
six lines in the incipit page (fol. 1r), divided into three groups, alternating with black lines;
two lines at paragraph beginning on fol. 23v;
some words on fol. 11r, l.11;
elements of the Ethiopian numerals and of punctuation signs;
the words “sänbät” and “sälam” and their abbreviations.
